        section
            h1 INDUCTIVE BASIS
            aside
                time Published: 27 JAN 2022
            p.
               These types form the inductive basis of MLTT foundations
               and are built-in into type checker.

            h1 EMPTY
            p.
                The Empty type represents False-type logical 𝟎, type without inhabitants, Void or ⊥ (Bottom).
                As it has not inhabitants it lacks both constructors and eliminators, however, it has induction.
            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Empty-type 𝟎). Empty-type is defined as built-in 𝟎-type.
                $$
                    𝟎 : U
                $$
            code.
                def Empty : U := 𝟎
            br.

            h2 Induction Principle
            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Induction Principle $ind_0$). 𝟎-type is satisfying the
                induction principle:
                $$
                    \prod_{C\ :\ 𝟎\ \rightarrow\ U} \prod_{z\ :\ 𝟎} C(z) := ind_0(C(z),z).
                $$
            br.
            code.
                def Empty-ind (C: 𝟎 → U) (z: 𝟎) : C z := ind₀ (C z) z
            br.

            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Negation or isEmpty). For any type A negation of A is defined as arrow from A to 𝟎.
                $$
                   \neg A := A \rightarrow 𝟎.
                $$
            code.
                def isEmpty (A: U): U := A → 𝟎
            p.
                The witness of $\neg A$ is obtained by assuming A and deriving a contradiction.
                This techniques is called proof of negation and is constructive in constrast
                to non-constructive proof by contradiction which implies $\neg\neg A \rightarrow A$ (double negation elimination).
            br

            h1 UNIT
            p.
                Unit type is the simplest type equipped with full set of MLTT inference rules.
                It contains single inhabitant ★ (Star).
            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Unit-type 𝟏). Unit-type is defined as built-in 𝟏-type.
                $$
                    𝟏 : U.
                $$
            code.
                def Unit : U := 𝟏
            br.

            h2 Constructor
            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Star). 𝟏-type containts single inhabitant ★:
                $$
                     ★ : 𝟏.
                $$
            code.
                def 1-ctor : 𝟏 := ★

            h2 Induction Principle
            p.
                <b>Definition</b> (Induction Principle $ind_1$). 𝟏-type satisfies
                induction principle that for any family $P(x)$ indexed by $x : 1$ there is a function
                $$
                    \prod_{C\ :\ 𝟏\ \rightarrow\ U} \prod_{x\ :\ C(★)} \prod_{z\ :\ 𝟏} C(z) := ind_1(C,x,z).
                $$
            code.
                def 1-ind (C: 𝟏 → U) (x: C ★) (z: 𝟏) : C z := ind₁ C x z
            br

